shit: 3:18: warning: 2>&1 before the file redirect duplicates the terminal, so stderr stays on the terminal.
     3 |    command 2>&1 > out.log
       |                   ^~~~~~~ here.
note: Put the file redirect first as in '>file 2>&1'.
shit: 4:17: warning: The command reads and truncates 'data' at once, the truncation empties the input before it is read.
     4 |    sort < data > data
       |                  ^~~~ here.
note: Write to a temporary and move it over.
shit: 5:8: warning: A command substitution wraps a useless echo.
     5 |    echo "wrapped $(echo inner)"
       |         ^~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~ here.
note: The text can be used directly without the subshell.
shit: 6:15: warning: $@ inside a longer word concatenates the surrounding text onto the first and last argument.
     6 |    printf '%s' "a $@ b"
       |                ^~~~~~~~ here.
note: Use $* for one joined string or a separate "$@" word.
done
